ğŸ§  What is a JavaScript Object?

An **object** is a data structure that stores data in **keyâ€“value pairs**.

```js
let user = {
  name: "Saakshi",
  age: 21,
  role: "Developer"
};
```

ğŸ“Œ Keys â†’ properties
ğŸ“Œ Values â†’ data

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ†š Object vs Array

| Object              | Array            |
| ------------------- | ---------------- |
| Key-value pairs     | Indexed values   |
| Represents entities | Represents lists |
| `{}` syntax         | `[]` syntax      |

