```

ğŸ“Œ Prefer **object literal**

---

ğŸ” Accessing Object Properties

Dot Notation

```js
console.log(user.name);
```

Bracket Notation

```js
console.log(user["age"]);
```

ğŸ“Œ Bracket notation is useful for dynamic keys

---

âœï¸ Modifying Object Properties

```js
user.age = 22;
user.city = "Delhi"; // add new property
```

---

âŒ Deleting Properties

```js
